<headline>Winter Storm Warning issued January 06 at 3:29AM EST until January 07 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 7 PM
EST SUNDAY...
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 12
inches with locally higher amounts up to 15 inches.
* WHERE....Lake George and Saratoga Regions and the Southern
Adirondacks
* WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 7 PM EST Sunday.
* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult due to snow covered
roadways and reduced visibility.
* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snowfall rates around one inch per hour at
times for Saturday evening into early Sunday morning.</description>
<instruction>If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.</instruction>
